
*** fpc1020 Linux driver simple testscript ***

Prerequisites:
- Kernel prepared to accept fpc1020 on SPIx.
- fpc1020 device driver, compiled as a kernel module or built-into the kernel.

Usage:
- Modify fpc1020_envsetup.sh to fit the current environment.
- Create a work directory on the platform.
- Copy all files, fpc1020*.sh, to the platform work directory.
- Copy the kernel driver module, fpc1020.ko to the platform work directory.
- Execute fpc1020_main.sh

Notes:
- This is an engineering tool, intended for basic sensor connectivity testing.
- Superuser permissions are required on the target platform.


